// Is edges[0][0] (which is 1) equal to edges[1][0] (which is 2)? -> No.
// Is edges[0][0] (which is 1) equal to edges[1][1] (which is 3)? -> No.

// Since '1' did not repeat in the second edge, it cannot be the center.
// Therefore, the program immediately hits the final statement:
// return edges[0][1]; // returns 2

